  {
    "id": "halfway park__Regarding_-_Security_Director_Arthur_Ford",
    "source": "Halfway Park/Regarding - Security Director Arthur Ford.json",
    "title": "<b>Regarding - Security Director Arthur Ford</b>",
    "body": "<line-indent=10%>The Nullmen took to the void-fermented melon juice pretty quickly, the effects are interesting. We’ll keep making sure to keep import routes open but I’m not sure how long we can keep it under the radar.\r\n<br><br>\r\nYour boss is absolutely aware and hasn’t made any attempts to shut us down… he is on our side here. I will have to reach out at some point or maybe you should call him?\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe main thing that has me concerned are the Nulls in the time tower constructing a Void Gate, talk about following the white rabbit… All of MythOS will be blown wide open if they succeed, but that could be cool.\r\n<br><br>\r\nI’ll keep as many back doors open as I can but whoever started it is hopefully going to continue as well.\r\n<br><br>\r\n- GS\r\n<br>\n‎",
    "level": "halfway park"
  },
  {
    "id": "halfway park__Stress_Relief",
    "source": "Halfway Park/Stress Relief.json",
    "title": "<b>Stress Relief</b>",
    "body": "<line-indent=10%>I made the printer’s replicable specifically to smash them.\r\n<br><br>\r\nEvery day for lunch I smash a printer.\r\n<br><br>\r\nEvery break I smash a printer.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSmashing the printers reduces my stress. If Chris spent less time at the MoTD I think he’d find therapeutic benefits to smashing printers.\r\n<br><br>\r\n- GS\r\n<br>\n‎",
    "level": "halfway park"
  },
  {
    "id": "halfway park__Working_in_the_Park",
    "source": "Halfway Park/Working in the Park.json",
    "title": "<b>Working in the Park</b>",
    "body": "<line-indent=10%>Hey Hayes! I am loving the park office setup.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAfter security removed the rail system from the industrial park, the commute from District 06 for lunch breaks was just too much. I do wish they would bring the tram back but for now the park office is great.\r\n<br><br>\r\nI’ve made some progress on the tech you requested. The portable Elevator was a great (albeit hacky) idea, but I think some of these tools are really going to come in handy for developing void city infrastructure.\r\n<br><br>\r\nWe hope to have updates on exhibits as improvements are completed in MythOS City Development.\r\n<br><br>\r\n- GS\r\n<br>\n‎",
    "level": "halfway park"
  },
  {
    "id": "mirror__Void_Mirrors_12",
    "source": "Mirror/Void Mirrors 12.json",
    "title": "<b>Void Mirrors 1/2</b>",
    "body": "Mirrors are hypnotizing but exceptionally calming.\r\n<br><br>\r\nWhen I began working on my research of the void mirrors and moved into this chamber, I wasn’t fully convinced of the almost addictive properties that others have described with mirrors. I am now beginning to understand the draw and power they have. I don’t even feel like leaving.. So I began to setup an even more advanced work lab here on site. Working in such close proximity to the mirror will allow me to really dive into the magic of these things.\r\n<br><br>\r\nNate\r\n<br>\n‎",
    "level": "mirror"
  },
  {
    "id": "mirror__Void_Mirrors_22",
    "source": "Mirror/Void Mirrors 22.json",
    "title": "<b>Void Mirrors 2/2</b>",
    "body": "<br>\r\nI understand the reflections are actually just a boid swarm, forming the shape of what they reflect… though I do feel a sense of connection to these manifestations. It’s like they know how I feel and are trying to get to the very core of my being… I will need to continue researching before I type out anything so ridiculous as that again.\r\n<br><br>\r\nNate\r\n<br>\n‎",
    "level": "mirror"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__Comms_Board_2",
    "source": "Museum Basement/Comms Board 2.json",
    "title": "Comms Board",
    "body": "Data Encrypted",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__EMPLOYER_APPRECIATION",
    "source": "Museum Basement/EMPLOYER APPRECIATION.json",
    "title": "<b>EMPLOYER APPRECIATION</b>",
    "body": "I am so happy I got this job in the Museum Archives! <br><br> What an honor it has been to secure Monogon proprietary museum data ! <br><br> I heard there may be a group of separatists sifting through and modifying structural components to the underlying structure of MythOS… They must be stopped, that's terrible! <br><br> At least I know they aren’t in HALFWAY PARK, that is where I go on my lunch breaks and its always carefully monitored. <br> This is the best job ever! <br><br> Thank you Monogon!, <br> -Chris <br><br>",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__Encrypted_Equipment",
    "source": "Museum Basement/Encrypted Equipment.json",
    "title": "<b>Encrypted Equipment</b>",
    "body": "<line-indent=10%><color=black>S: I’m finishing up some additional work on the encrypted PC equipment.</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<color=#1D0707>C: Thanks, I will feel safer about digging and shipping this stuff out once I know my equipment isn’t logging everything I do.</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<color=black>S: Even after the broad security sweep of the museum, Alora has no idea who we are or that we’re working down here.</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<color=#1D0707>C: District six was a major hotzone after the security director things so even if we’re in a low population instance, I don’t feel truly safe from prying eyes.</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<color=black>S: Don’t be too paranoid, we aren’t here for much longer anyways.</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n‎",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__Exporting_Data_Plates_-_FOUND_IT_",
    "source": "Museum Basement/Exporting Data Plates - FOUND IT!.json",
    "title": "<color=#1D0707><b>Exporting Data Plates - FOUND IT!</b></color>",
    "body": "<line-indent=10%><color=#1D0707>C: I think we got it! How do we get this out of here?!</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<color=black>S: WHAT really!? Alright keep cool keep cool.. We can either go through one of the LavaGang door tunnels or we could try that spawnable elevator Hayes made.</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<color=#1D0707>C: There is absolutely no way we’re fitting this on an elevator. We’re going to need to truck it through a door but I’m worried how slow that is going to be. Definitely going to blip on some radars…</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<color=black>S: Guess I’ll start packing some guns.</color>\r\n<br><br>\r\n‎",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__HELP_HELP_",
    "source": "Museum Basement/HELP HELP!.json",
    "title": "<b>HELP HELP!</b>",
    "body": "Hello? Hello? Please, a chance for redemption is all I beg!  <br><br> Myth, please hear me! <br><br> Send me a savior! <br><br> I Thought the archive was a prison, how wrong I was <br> To be forsaken in this forgotten dungeon is a far greater punishment <br><br> Please send me to the flame <br> Clippee, the clipboard <br><br>",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__MUSEUM_BASEMENT_ARCHIVAL_INCINERATION",
    "source": "Museum Basement/MUSEUM BASEMENT ARCHIVAL INCINERATION.json",
    "title": "<b>MUSEUM BASEMENT ARCHIVAL / INCINERATION</b>",
    "body": "After the security director escaped into the void, Monogon has become exceedingly paranoid about infosec. <br><br> They’ve tasked me with simply throwing away discarded museum parts into the incinerator and cataloging info pull requests. <br><br> I think anyone that requests info is immediately investigated and possibly terminated… <br><br> This paranoia is too much. <br> I’m not sure how much longer I can swing this. <br><br> -Chris <br><br>",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__Office_of_Outreach_-_Museum_GiftShop_Memo",
    "source": "Museum Basement/Office of Outreach - Museum GiftShop Memo.json",
    "title": "<b>Office of Outreach - Museum GiftShop Memo</b>",
    "body": "<line-indent=10%>GiftShop Products:\r\n<br>\nUltraMersion Basketballs - Selling well despite lack of available courts and hoops within the city. Perhaps this is something to bring up for future development research? 25 units on hand.\r\n<br>\nSwords & Spiders - We can’t seem to keep any Sword&Spiders blind boxes in stock, they keep selling out and are proving difficult to come by. Perhaps we should open an exhibit for the game?\r\n<br>\nApollo Toys - People keep asking if they can purchase the BIG Apollo figure, so there should be an official inquiry into a possible limited run of the light probe god statues?\r\n<br>\nNoodleDog - The noodly foam swords are absolutely our number one seller, however there are rumors of a recall on the product due to a very rare bug where the safety sword can become an unstoppable destructive weapon. We haven’t seen anything like that happen with our stock but the concern is still there. \r\n<br>\n- Steve!\r\n<br>\n‎",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__Office_of_Outreach_-_Museum_of_Technical_Demonstration",
    "source": "Museum Basement/Office of Outreach - Museum of Technical Demonstration.json",
    "title": "<b>Office of Outreach - Museum of Technical Demonstration</b>",
    "body": "<line-indent=10%>Designs for the opening day posters are coming along nicely. We’ll need to run the video ad edits by legal, to be sure everything looks good.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAll rejected promotional materials are to be sent to Trash Handlers for recycling.\r\n<br><br>\r\nMythOS opening day is expected to be a big event and the hope is to hold annual celebrations, so these materials will be necessary for future promotions.\r\n<br><br>\r\nWe hope to have updates on exhibits as improvements are completed in MythOS City Development.\r\n<br><br>\r\n- Steve!\r\n<br>\n‎",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__REDACTED_INFO_RETURN",
    "source": "Museum Basement/REDACTED INFO RETURN.json",
    "title": "<b>REDACTED INFO RETURN</b>",
    "body": "Monogon continues to update the mechanics exhibit, sending older pieces down here. <br><br> Breaking the mechanics into tablet fragments, I can send them without drawing attention. <br><br> If they start searching for anyone working on forked mechanics, you might be done for… <br><br> Please let me know when I can return to the lab, this basement is starting to get creepy. <br> Hopefully we can split out into the void and build something new asap <br><br> Thanks, <br> -Chris <br><br>",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "museum basement__Void_Puddles",
    "source": "Museum Basement/Void Puddles.json",
    "title": "Void Puddles",
    "body": "The archival information available on the purple void puddles and energy particles are either extremely lacking or extremely guarded. This is what I was able to collect:\n<br><br>\nMonogon inquiry returns: Void Leaks are a heightened concentration of Void Energy. This substance is believed to be the \"glue\" which binds material matter. These leaks can appear for a variety of reasons known and unknown though most often found at sites of removed/destroyed static geometry. Cleaning and patching of leaks is possible through [REDACTED] however most will seal on their own, given enough time. \n<br><br>\nVoid Energy off-gassing can pose a dangerous threat to entities due to [REDACTED]. Caution is advised. Please alert Monogon Clean-Up Crew or Trash Handlers if there is a suspected leak in your vicinity.",
    "level": "museum basement"
  },
  {
    "id": "neon district tac trial__Sabrelake_Weapon_Assets",
    "source": "Neon District Tac Trial/Sabrelake Weapon Assets.json",
    "title": "<b>Sabrelake Weapon Assets</b>",
    "body": "Sabrelake’s firearms always have an absurd rate of fire. Weapon labs need to progress further with testing to really see what this math is capable of.\r\n<br><br>\r\nAdjusted and heavily modified guns can start pushing physics into wild unknown territory..exciting stuff.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe warehouse should support these kinds of things but we really need to evaluate the implications for testing.. Do these present too different variables for accurate data collection?\r\n<br><br>\r\nKW\r\n<br><br>",
    "level": "neon district tac trial"
  },
  {
    "id": "neon district tac trial__Work_Commute",
    "source": "Neon District Tac Trial/Work Commute.json",
    "title": "<b>Work Commute</b>",
    "body": "MythOS was actually a fantastic workaround for long commute times. Being able to work in the office from home has reduced my carbon footprint measurably.\r\n<br><br>\r\nI do miss the ability to zone out in traffic while jamming to music though.. I wonder if people see load-times as the new traffic.\r\n<br><br>\r\nWe still need to update the ways of piping music into here… hmm\r\n<br><br>\r\nKW\r\n<br><br>",
    "level": "neon district tac trial"
  },
  {
    "id": "rooftops__Deja_Vu",
    "source": "Rooftops/Deja Vu.json",
    "title": "<b>Deja Vu</b>",
    "body": "Okay I know I’ve seen this architecture somewhere before… \r\n<br><br>\r\nEither the design AI is using our memories or dreams to form these locations. I have been here before, I have seen this in my head.\r\n<br><br>\r\nThe security implications with this feels… invasive. I think I need to consult with the BONEWORKS team to see what they think or if they even have any idea about this at all.\r\n<br><br>\r\nSJ\r\n<br><br>",
    "level": "rooftops"
  },
  {
    "id": "tuscany__OldMyth_Testing",
    "source": "Tuscany/OldMyth Testing.json",
    "title": "<b>OldMyth Testing</b>",
    "body": "I miss Old Myth\n<br><br>\nEveryone else who remembers those days, only remembers the crude and rudimentary AI attempts.\n<br><br>\nAge of root? Measurement of physical distance? A seed value? Some kind of void-based molecular composition we are unaware of? Maybe similar material signatures?\n<br>\nIt is clear the lower the levels stack and further the tendrils spread, not only is the iteration count lower but the space becomes more abstracted. Not only does the space have a more unfinished / uninhabited / liminal feel to it, but the sense of danger and fragility increases.\n<br><br>\n\n\n<br><br>",
    "level": "tuscany"
  }
